  "prompt": "How do I add more than one WordPress site in Godaddy's Deluxe hosting plan?",
  "response": "Adding more than one WordPress site to GoDaddy's Deluxe hosting plan can be accomplished by following these steps:\n\n### 1. **Log in to Your GoDaddy Account**\n   - Go to the GoDaddy website and log in to your account.\n\n### 2. **Access Your Hosting Account**\n   - Navigate to your \"My Products\" page.\n   - Under \"Web Hosting,\" find the Deluxe plan you want to use and click on \"Manage.\"\n\n### 3. **Use the cPanel or Managed WordPress Dashboard**\n   - Depending on your hosting type (cPanel or Managed WordPress), the steps will vary slightly.\n\n#### For cPanel Hosting:\n1. **Access the cPanel**:\n   - You will be redirected to your hosting account\u2019s cPanel dashboard.\n\n2. **Create a New Database (Optional)**:\n   - If you want to keep each WordPress site in its own database, go to the \"MySQL Databases\" section.\n   - Create a new database and user for each site.\n\n3. **Install WordPress**:\n   - Go back to the cPanel dashboard and find the **Softaculous Apps Installer** (or similar).\n   - Click on WordPress, then select the option to install it.\n   - Fill in the required information, such as the domain name (if using a subdomain or add-on domain), site name, admin username, and password.\n\n4. **Repeat for Additional Sites**:\n   - Repeat the installation process for each additional WordPress site you wish to create.\n\n#### For Managed WordPress Hosting:\n1. **Access the Managed WordPress Dashboard**:\n   - In your GoDaddy account, go to \"My Products\" and find your Managed WordPress plan.\n\n2. **Add a New Site**:\n   - Click on **Add Site** or **Add WordPress Site**.\n   - Follow the prompts to set up the new WordPress site, including selecting a domain or subdomain and filling in the necessary information.\n\n3. **Manage Your Sites**:\n   - You can manage all your WordPress sites from the Managed WordPress dashboard.\n\n### 4. **Domain Setup**\n- **Subdomains**: If you're adding sites under the same main domain, consider using subdomains (e.g., blog.yourdomain.com).\n- **Add-on Domains**: If you\u2019re using separate domains, you may need to set them up as add-on domains in your cPanel.\n\n### 5. **SSL Certificates**\n- Ensure that you have SSL certificates configured for each site, especially if they are live. GoDaddy often provides free SSL certificates for your domains.\n\n### 6. **Install Themes and Plugins**\n- After setting up each WordPress site, you can log in to each site\u2019s admin panel (e.g., yourdomain.com/wp-admin) to install themes and plugins as needed.\n\n### 7. **Backup and Maintenance**\n- Regularly back up your WordPress sites and perform necessary updates for themes and plugins for security and performance.\n\n### Conclusion\nBy following these steps, you can successfully host multiple WordPress sites on GoDaddy's Deluxe hosting plan. If you encounter any issues, GoDaddy\u2019s customer support can provide further assistance.",
